      - updated version information (outdated)

   - PageStream:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import (loader)
      - increased library requirements (loader/saver)

   - AdPro:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import (loader)
      - increased library requirements (loader/saver)
      - added AdPro.cpinfo (see library)

 - Tools:

   - WinSlide:

      - added option KEYCLOSE that can be combined
        with CLOSEGAD
      - fixed window title texts according to
        actual config (CLOSEGAD, KEYCLOSE, nothing)

   - JPEG-Box5:

      - now finally supports 48 bit import
      - optimized memory allocations
      - fixed HAM detection routine (forgotten copy-paste)
      - increased library requirements
      - Copyright bump to 2008 (and fix)
      - now calls WinSlide with KEYCLOSE, allows
        to close window by keypress

   - PNG-Box5:

      - fixed HAM detection routine (forgotten copy-paste)
      - increased library requirements
      - Copyright bump to 2008 (and fix)
      - upgraded to libpng 1.2.24
      - libpng config for 030 version now same as 000 version
        (tRNS handling)
      - now calls WinSlide with KEYCLOSE, allows
        to close window by keypress

   - GIF-Box5:

      - now finally rejects 48 bit import (like 24 bit)
      - fixed HAM detection routine (forgotten copy-paste)
      - increased library requirements
      - replaced wrong GUI gfx and removed it
      - Copyright bump to 2008 (and fix)
      - now calls WinSlide with KEYCLOSE, allows
        to close window by keypress

 - included sview5.library V14.6 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.38 (26.12.2007): (english)

 - now also supports import of RAW binary data, by pattern
   (see SView5-Library history and RAW-IMPORT.sv5object docs)
 - added rudimentary DefIcons support and a USE_DEFICONS
   switch which is enabled by default; fallback to SView5
   icons in case no deficon is found

 - included sview5.library V14.5 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.37 (25.12.2007): (english)

 - fixed some outdated library version information in guide files
 - fixed some bogus library version info in turkish and spanish .ct files;
   in some other .ct files only the outcommented original texts
 - updated all .ct files for new sview5.library minimum
 - increased sview5.library requirements to V14+
 - extra long meta info data no longer crashes wizard.library
   when opening picture info requester

 - included sview5.library V14.4 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.36 (8.12.2007): (english)

 - added v2.35 history in german guide file
 - added additional SETCP=... ARexx command which allows to
