V2.29 (13.7.2007): (english)

 - address change

 - added basic PREVIEW functionality, which can be
   activated for Slide View mode by clicking the
   checkbox beneath the corresponding button
 - this is not default, due to performance considerations
   and stability issues (BETA) but you can make it
   default within SView5.config

 - updated button help in .guide with preview function;
   detailed info can be found @{"there" LINK GADGET_View}

 - added PREVIEW / PREVIEW_SIZE [CTA] commands

 - again possible array size issue fixed

 - included sview5.library V13.5 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)
 - note, that V13.4 was not released yet, either

V2.28 (3.6.2007): (english)

 - added new sub-commands to GETINFO ARexx command:

    - for checking if a graphics is HAM6/HAM8 or EHB
    - for getting the 32 bit ViewMode (if valid)
    - for getting the 32 bit DIPF flags (if present);
      which again allows to check for e.g. HAM

   The idea here is, that an ARexx script may
   conditionally check if e.g. HAM inputs needs
   to be converted to e.g. 24 bit before doing
   anything else with the graphics data.

 - PNG-Box5: upgraded to libpng 1.2.18

 - included sview5.library V13.3 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.27 (23.5.2007): (english)

 - included sview5.library V13.2 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.26 (13.5.2007): (english)

