 - JPEG-Box5:    - increased library requirements

 - included sview5.library V13.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.25 (29.4.2007): (english)

 - added 48/64 bit indicator for SV modules on GUI
 - LOAD/SAVE now accept quotes
   (-> Ingo Schmitz)
 - made color selection 48 bit aware

 - included sview5.library V12.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.24 (15.4.2007): (english)

 - added LOADCONFIG/SAVECONFIG ARexx commands
 - added basic 48 bit support (see library history)
 - as part of this, introduced new IFF-ILBM 48/64 bit
   format, allowing for direct 16 Bit PNG<->ILBM conversion

 - included sview5.library V11.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.23 (31.3.2007): (english)

 - included sview5.library V10.12 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.22 (22.3.2007): (english)

 - included sview5.library V10.11 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.21 (17.3.2007): (english)

 - added some more sub-commands to GETINFO ARexx command

    - for retrieving SV module major versions)
    - for retrieving number of SV modules/types per category
    - for retrieving names of SV modules (and save types)
    - for retreiving graphics properties (gfxalpha)

    see "ARexx-Scripts/GetInfo.rx" for usage demo

 - fixed several bugs in the [CTA] code dealing with
   names (and related extensions) of modules ending /w
   .sv5object/.sv5driver/.sv5operator

 - the SQ operators are now available under their real name;
   this means the name is no longer operator_SQ but SQoperator

V2.20 (3.3.2007): (english)

 - included sview5.library V10.10 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.19 (28.2.2007): (english)

 - due to a missing gfxbuffer version check,
   the gfxbuffer info window could have reported
   "alpha" sometimes, even if the alpha information
   already had been stripped previously (e.g. by
   a 24 bit to 8 bit dithering operation)
 - optimized ARexx, WB Tooltypes and Config option
   parsing (faster)
 - added two new ARexx commands for saving screens,
   with wildcard support, i.e. now you can grab
   screens using a pattern like "ScreenName #?"
 - other minor optimizations

V2.18 (17.2.2007): (english)

 - removed STATUS ARexx command
 - added new "GETINFO=command" Arexx command, which
   allows to retrieve certain information (details
   specified by command); currently program/library
   version and basic GfxBuffer information can be
   retrieved, in the future more options may be added
   (=> @{"details" LINK Control})
 - completely reworked the content of the "ARexx-Scripts"
   folder (including the scripts themselves, the readme,
   and the annoying usage of T: - which is now VMEM:)
 - fixed bug with extra space at end of some file type
   names w/o subtype which would not have been available
   via ARexx due to the extra space (e.g. "DEEP ")
 - fixed older history entries slightly
 - installer script changes:

     - fixed percentages
     - sview5.library now always installed at last
     - no longer copies SViewIV config files in case
       there is no SView5 config file in ENV: or ENVARC:

 - included sview5.library V10.8 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.17 (12.2.2007): (english)

 - the first click on an AppIcon (without the main window
   being open) did cause an enforcer hit while trying to
   obtain the (pub)screen pointer

 - included sview5.library V10.7 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.16 (11.2.2007): (english)

 - name of the AppIcon now is "SView5"
 - properly defined AppIcon data as const
 - fixed array boundary problem with tooltypes which could
   cause all sorts of problems (since v2.10 probably)
   including crashes

V2.15 (11.2.2007): (english)

 - removed some debug code in config subs (SVDriver settings)
 - the SAVE_TYPE=... setting had the same (legacy) problem
   as SVDRIVER/SVOPERATOR, see previous version
   (-> Roland Heyder)
 - no longer attempts loading any SViewIV config files as fallback
 - no longer sets SViewIV as default tool in icons
 - fixed another minor issue related to the SVDRIVER=... setting
   (if not provided, the default library svdriver would not
    have been preset, either)

 - included sview5.library V10.6 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.14 (10.2.2007): (english)

 - there was still a bug in the new SVDriver configuration scheme;
   it could happen that always the global driver was used instead
   of the local one (-> Roland Heyder)
 - the SVDRIVER=... setting did not work (since switch to SView5)
   (-> Roland Heyder)
 - same for SVOPERATOR=...

 - included sview5.library V10.5 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.13 (9.2.2007): (english)

 - it is now possible to select predefined Convolve/ConvolveNxN
   matrix definition files easily over the GUI (overriding
   custom matrix settings, if wanted); you can place your own,
   new convolution matrix files under

    ENVARC:SView5-Library/Convolve/#?.controlpad
    ENVARC:SView5-Library/ConvolveNxN/#?.controlpad

  For ConvolveNxN, the size of the matrix must be included
  in the controlpad (see sample definition files), since
  5x5, 7x7 and 9x9 are allowed (normal Convolve is 3x3)

 - included sview5.library V10.4 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.12 (5.2.2007): (english)

 - included sview5.library V10.3 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.11 (4.2.2007): (english)

 - included sview5.library V10.2 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.10 (4.2.2007): (english)

 - Tools:

   - PNG-Box:

      - updated to libpng 1.2.15
      - increased minimum sview5.library requirements to V10
      - increased minimum sview5support.library requirements to V3
      - updated date and copyright information

   - JPEG-Box:

      - increased minimum sview5.library requirements to V10
      - increased minimum sview5support.library requirements to V3
      - updated date and copyright information

 - added two more checkbox gadgets, one for the Save button
   and one for symmetry (yet always disabled)
 - the checkbox button besides the Save button now activates
   the automatic generation of the default file extension
   (e.g. .ilbm/.png/.jpg) when opening the file requester
   prior to saving a file; note that it is still possible
   to just ignore this recommendation and change the file
   name not to have an extension; ARexx is not affected
   by the checkbox setting
 - opening any file requester now causes a busy mouse pointer
 - added new ARexx command "AREASELECT" for selecting an
   SVOperator action area via Arexx (instead of the GUI)
 - added support for new "AREA" .cpinfo data type, which
   allows to select an area visually and pass the
   rectangle coordinates as ControlPad parameter
   to SV#? modules in form "SV_AREA=left,top,width,height";
   e.g. as parameter to Cut/Crop SV5Operator;
   NOTE: this works on a real graphics visually only,
         in case there is one loaded (otherwise manually
         entering a string is required);
         any previously selected "global" area will be
         released, then; selection of a global area
         on the other hand will overwrite (delete)
         a previous local SV_AREA in the .controlpad
 - added support for new "COLOR_#?" .cpinfo data types,
   which allow to select a color/component visually and pass
   the result as ControlPad parameter to SV#? modules
   e.g. as parameter to AddAlpha SV5Operator;
   OR when e.g. selecting the transparent color of a GIF/PNG
   image prior to saving it (cf. GIF-Box5/PNG-Box5)
   NOTE: this works on a real graphics visually only,
         in case there is one loaded (otherwise manually
         entering a string is required)
 - results of SV5Operators which result in de-facto size changes
   will be rejected for area operations now (size mismatch error)
 - SV5Operators which have the -new- "size change" flag set,
   are rejected for area operations (size mismatch error)
 - the 4 CTA commands for ASL file requester dimension settings
   have been replaced by a single new one (you will have to
   redo your settings)
 - after using an ASL file requester the first time, size
   and position are not remembered (and saved into the configuration
   in case it is saved afterwards); no more need to manually hack
   it into your configuration file the first time
 - the default file requester size/pos now is always determined
   from the screen size using a simple formula
 - added new CTA command VISUAL_PREFS for controlling the new
   visual area/color selection mechanism (on/off - default is on)
 - the SV5Driver settings are no longyer globally changed for
   all programs, but only locally within SView5 (regardless
   whether changed on the GUI, via Config or via Arexx)
 - increased minimum sview5.library requirements to V10
 - also updated the .guide file regarding sview5(support).library
   minimum requirements
 - etc. etc. etc.
 - included sview5.library V10.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

V2.00 (14.1.2007): (english)

 - fixed a number of icon positions
 - removed obsolete options from SView5.cpinfo
 - added two (four) new buttons for 2 new features;
   one yet remains disabled
 - added unlimited UNDO functionality (uses VMEM:)
 - added two more checkboxes to the GUI which allow
   for automatic display (when enabled) of
   graphics right after "Load" or "Action";
   this saves you from pressing "View" each time
 - slightly re-arranged the existing buttons to
   make the new checkboxes fit at the right places
 - updated spanish guide and GUI catalog (-> Damaso Dominguez)
 - added missing protection bits to Quickstart batch files
   (-> Damaso Dominguez)
 - now explicitely copy all the Quickstart files including
   icons when creating the LHA (no more pattern matching -
   wonder who wrote that part for MorphOS/FFS)
   (-> Damaso Dominguez)
 - extended german/english guide with online help for
   new GUI buttons (also added support in code)
 - minimum requirements increased to sview5.library V9+
   and sview5support.library V3+
 - fixed sv#? library-version related texts in all catalogs;
   fixed some bogus texts in some, while at it
 - included sview5.library V9.1 (see history in SView5-Library Guide)

