V1.72 (30.5.2006): (english)

 - ASL multi-selection does not work under the WB of AOS4/MOS which
   caused the filerequester of CyberSlide, SuperSlide, ScrollSlide
   and WinSlide not to deliver any selection results at all;
   added fallback-option in case the multi-selection result
   is zero - in this case the single-selection will be taken;
   CLI usage was not affected

V1.71 (13.4.2006): (english)

 - included updated sview5.library V5.2

V1.70 (26.2.2006): (english)

 - SView5: - 24 Bit and Alpha (32 Bit) support now is
             indicated on the GUI (for SVObject Savers)

           - starting from sview5.library V5
             SView5 uses its own internal info requester,
             which is font-sensitive, provides additional
             information and allows to change the viewmode
             (with older library versions it uses the
              old approach, which is driven by the SVObjects)

 - included updated sview5.library V5.1

V1.67 (4.2.2006): (english)

 - included updated sview5.library with some new operators:

     - AlphaBlend
     - FixAlphaBlend
     - AddAlpha
     - InvertAlpha
     - StripAlpha
     - ExtractAlpha
     - AddTransColor

 - PPaint plugin:

     - no longer saves settings to ENVARC: (only ENV:)
     - fixed some compatibility issues with sview5.library
     - now imports and exports single-color transparency
       for (upto) 8 bit images
     - all the loaders/savers now start with "SV5" instead
       of "SV" and the priority was decreased from 9000
       to 8999 - this should fix problems when the old
       sview io library is installed in parallel

 - AdPro plugin:

     - Loader: now imports alpha channel into AdPro, if present
     - Saver:  unfortunately export is not possible (not documented)

 - Tools:

     - fixed PNG-Box5, JPEG-Box5 and GIF-Box5 copyright & layout
     - fixed TRNS check in PNG-/GIF-Box5
     - PNG-Box now indicates multi-color transparency PNGs
     - PNg-Box now allows to modify PNG filter settings

 - SView5:

     - fixed problem with spaces in pathnames when calling external player
       or executing rexx scripts from menu
     - fixed garbage wildcard in certain file requesters associated
       with .cpinfo preferences settings
     - strip control characters from viewmode name before loading, saving
       or processing it (e.g. under MOS this may occur)

